@node "Introduction" "Introduction"


@{b}Introduction@{ub}


Amiga is still alive mainly for one reason: @{b}Aminet@{ub}!!

Aminet is the largest, most important and well known collection of freely
distribut able Amiga software. Up to 10.000 users access the Aminet
archives daily and countless programmers publish their masterpieces via
Aminet.

And today AmyGate makes browsing thru Aminet easier and easier!!


It supports:

 - Most recent uploads

 - Last seven days' upload

 - Aminet charts

 - Search of a file

 - Rating programs

 - Upload (not working yet)

 - Aminet Mailing-list

And all this in the most user-friendly way you can imagine!

All files are sorted automatically in the "tree form" of the Aminet archive.
@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"


@{b}Distribution@{ub}


This program is @{u}FREEWARE@{uu}: you can distribute, copy and do anything
you like with it without paying anything, as long as you don't sell it or
make money on it.

Anyway I'd like to receive a @{b}postcard@{ub} from you if you like and use AmyGate.

AmyGate is not Public Domain: it is Copyright by Pietro Ghizzoni and any
modification to the code or to the original archive is explicitly prohibited.



@{b}Use it at your own risk!@{ub}


Althought AmyGate has been extensively tested, there could be nasty bugs lying
around. You cannot hold the author responsable for any kind of damage that
AmyGate may cause.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"


@{b}Requirements@{ub}


Actually not much...

 - Amiga (of course)

 - Internet connection (of course... again!)

 - easylife.library (included in the archive with AmyGate)


That's it!
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"


@{b}Installation@{ub}


An installation tool is not provided in the archive with AmyGate for a very
simple reason: you don't need it to install because it's very easy!

Copy the easylife.library in your LIBS: drawer and then copy the whole
AmyGate directory wherever you want. You're ready!
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"


@{b}Usage@{ub}


When you run AmyGate a window with 9 gadgets pops up. You can read the
meaning of each gadget on the window border simply moving the mouse pointer
on it. You can also activate each gadget pressing F1 - F9 keys.


@{u}About...@{uu}
  It shows a requester with informations about AmyGate.


@{u}Recent Uploads@{uu}
  This is the most important and powerful feature of AmyGate. A window pops
  up and you can browse thru the newest Aminet files, already sorted in a
  tree format. You can use the mouse or the keyboard.

    - arrow up/down: change directory
    - arrow left/right: change file
    - enter or left button: download selected archive

  If you press the right button on the list of files a pop-up menu appers:

    - Download file: download the selected file
    - View Readme: download and show the readme file
    - Rate program: rate the selected program, adding automatically
      the name with the full path in the rate window. See below to know
      more about the rate window.
    - Bookmark: add the selected file in the bookmark window. See below
      about the bookmark window.

  If you press the right button on the list of directories, a pop-up menu
  appears with the Read command: this allows you to download the full list
  of files in the selected directory. This list is kept in the cache of
  AmyGate and can be read whenever you want or updated with the gadget
  Update.

  If you press the right button in the Network Status window, a pop-up
  menu appears and you can decide to disconnect automatically at the end
  of the download: in this way you don't need to wait, but can do other
  tasks.

  You can abort a download at any time selecting it with the mouse and
  pressing the Abort button. If you had already started downloading a file,
  a requester will pop up, giving you the chance to Cancel the download,
  Rename the new file or Resume the old download.

  If you press the Update button, AmyGate download the list of the uploads
  since your last call, and updates the list of files in the listviews. If
  there is not any new file, AmyGate will keep on showing the old list of
  files.

  The Hide button hides the download status window. You can restore it
  pressing the key "h".


@{u}Last Seven Days' Uploads@{uu}
  It works exactly like the recent Uploads, but it shows all the archives
  uploaded to Aminet in the last seven days.


@{u}Upload a file@{uu}
  This is still ghosted and is going to be added in the next version.


@{u}Charts@{uu}
  AmyGate downloads from Aminet the list of the most downloaded files and
  shows them in a separate window. In this way you can see which are the most
  common, popular and successful programs on Aminet. If AmyGate cannot
  download the latest list, it shows the last one in the cache.


@{u}Search a file@{uu}
  A little window pops up, where you can enter a string to search. You can
  enter here whatever string you want to search and then press the little icon
  with the magnifying lens. A window like those used for Recent Uploads and
  Last Seven Days' Upload pops up, with all the files containing the searched
  string in the name of the archive or in the first line of the reame file.
  You can stop the search at any time pressing the icon with the hand.


@{u}Bookmarks@{uu}
  A window pops up with all the bookmarked files. If you press the right mouse
  button a pop-up window appears with all the available options: you can
  download the selected file, view its reame file, rate it, remove it from the
  bookmark list or empty the bookmark list. There is also a gadget named Queue:
  this sets the maximum number of files downloaded at the same time. For
  instance, if you have 5 files in the bookmark and Queue is set to 2, AmyGate
  downloads the first 2 files, then when one of these is over, it starts
  downloading the third and so on. You can change the order of the files in
  the bookmark list with the arrows left and right. The list of bookmarked
  file is saved when you quit AmyGate.
  

@{u}Rate a program@{uu}
  A little window pops up with a string where you must insert the name (with
  full path!) of the program you want to rate and a number where you insert
  the rate (from 1 to 10). Click on the first button to rate the selected
  program.


@{u}Preferences@{uu}
  See the @{"preference" link "Preferences" 0} page.


@{u}Menus@{uu}
  The Mailing list menu has 4 items to subscribe and unsubscribe the weekly
  or the daily Aminet mailing list. You have just to select the action you
  want to do and AmyGate will perform it for you.
@endnode

@node "Preferences" "Preferences"


@{b}Preferences@{ub}


@{i}Toolbar Icons@{ui}

You can choose between 3 different sets of icons: MagicWb, GlowIcon1
and GlowIcon2. You can do it clicking the right mouse button over the
preference icon in the main window: a pop up menu will appear with these
three options.


@{i}Program Settings@{ui}


@{u}Your Name@{uu}:      your real name... quite easy so far!

@{u}E-mail@{uu}:         your email address... of course!

@{u}Mail server@{uu}:    your SMTP server, the same you use to send your emails.

@{u}Proxy & Port@{uu}:   if you want to use a proxy server, here we go. If you leave
                it blank, proxy won't be used. You can also enable/disable
                the proxy server using the check gadget placed between the
                address of the server and the port number.

@{u}Aminet Server@{uu}:  choose the closest server to you... or the fastest!

@{u}Miami@{uu}:          if you mark this check gadget the built-in
                miami support will be used. AmyGate will ask you if you
                want to go on-line when you start it(... if Miami is offline)
                and if you want to disconnect when you quit AmyGate.
                @{b}Note:@{ub} You must activate this function if you want to use
                the auto offline feature when all the file transfers are completed



@{u}Aminet Dir@{uu}:     In the list of Aminet Servers (read above) there are just
                some of the most important Aminet server and these are used for
                all the operations of AmyGate. Anyway you can decide to download
                the files from another server, maybe because it's faster: in this
                case type its address here. @{b}IMPORTANT:@{ub} you must
                specify the complete address of the main Aminet directory, and not
                just the server. A tipical example is the UK mirror:

                uk.aminet.net/aminet/dirs/aminet/

                In order to enable/disable the server use the check gadget
                placed on the right.

@{u}Viewer@{uu}:         this is used to display .readme files. You must insert the
                full path of it (for instance SYS:Utilities/Multiview). The
                ? button will make a requester pop up to choose the viewer.

@{u}Download@{uu}:       enter the directory where you want to download all your files.
                As above, the ? button will make a requester pop up to
                choose it.

@{u}Aminet Log@{uu}:     leave it blank the first time and AmyGate will fill it for you
                the first time. Anyway if you have already a log, you have to
                insert it here. For instance, if you access Aminet with a  
                string like: http://de.aminet.net/aminetbin/recent?42764 you
                have to insert 42764. If you change the Aminet server, you
                have to use another log: anyway AmyGate will keep in cache
                the old one if you decide to switch back to the previous
                server.


That's it... quite easy, isn't it?


@endnode

@node "Bugs" "Bugs"


@{b}Bugs@{ub}


As far as I know AmyGate is bug-free, but you know... coders like to leave
a bug or two in every program to see who's the fastest user to find them!

So if you find any bug, please report it to @{"me" link "Author" 0}!
@endnode

