@node "History" "History"


@{b}History@{ub}


@{b}V1.1a  (24-Feb-2001)@{ub}

 - Fixed the bug in the download routine. If the built-in Miami support wasn't activated, AmyGate
   always fails during the file transfers

 - Now the ampersands tag &amp; is correctly displayed


@{b}V1.1   (12-Feb-2001)@{ub}

 - Fixed the mungwall hits during the program exit. Now the progam is 100% hits free!

 - Fixed a little bug in the HTML parser... now ALL the uploads are listed

 - Now the URL is saved as comment to the downloaded file

 - Added the bubble help feature

 - During the program exit, the windows position are saved

 - Added the built-in Miami support. It allows you to go on/offline when
   required, and the possibility to automatically disconnet when all the
   file transfers are completed

 - Added the queue feature in the bookmark. Now you can specify the
   maximum number of files downloaded simultaneously

 - Added the possibility to read the whole content of the specified Aminet
   directory, and browse it

 - Added the user defined Aminet server. AmyGate will use the main
   servers for the basic operations, but now you can specify your
   prefered server for download. Read the doc first!

 - Improved the file transfer speed, and added the % display in the
   network status listview

 - Reworked the c2p routines. Now the icons should looks better, expecially
   with the OS 3.5 and 3.9

 - Changed the prefs file format! I'm sorry but you've to reconfigure the
   program. Not a big problem... just 1 minute! Remember to take a note of your
   Aminet Code if you're already registered!!!
 

@{b}V1.0 First Public Release@{ub}


@endnode

